*PhD position in Engineering and Computer Science: Machine Learning for 
Computational Fluid Dynamics

Sorbonne Université, Paris, Fr, Sorbonne Center for Artificial Intelligence


More information 
:***https://mlia.lip6.fr/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Machine-Learning-Computational-Fluid-Dynamics-PhD.pdf** 


*
*

**

*Advisors and contacts*: 
paola.cinnella@sorbonne-universite.fr<mailto:julien.salomon@inria.fr>(Institut 
Jean le Rond d'Alembert), patrick.gallinari@sorbonne-universite.fr 
(Laboratoire d’informatique de Paris 6)

*Starting date*: October 2021

*Duration*: 3 years

*Keywords*: Computational Fluid Dynamics, Machine Learning, Deep Neural 
Networks


Numerical simulation of fluids plays an essential role in modeling 
complex physical phenomena in domains ranging from climate to 
aerodynamics. Fluid flows are well described by Navier-Stokes equations, 
but solving these equations at all scales remains extremely complex in 
many situations. The increased availability of large amounts of high 
fidelity data and the recent development of powerful machine learning 
methods has motivated a surge of recent work for using machine learning 
in the context of computational fluid dynamics (CFD). The objective of 
the thesis is to develop the interplay between Deep Learning (DL) and 
CFD in order to improve turbulence modeling and to challenge state of 
the art ML techniques.


    Candidate profile

Master or engineering degree in engineering, computer science or applied 
mathematics. The topic is at the crossroad of computational fluid 
dynamics and machine learning . The candidate should have a strong 
scientific background with specialization in one of the two domains, 
good technical skills in programming. Experience of project development 
with machine learning platforms such as PyTorch or TensorFlow is a plus.


    Application

Send a CV, motivation letter and if possible recommendation letters or 
contacts to paola.cinnella@sorbonne-universite.fr and patrick.gallinari@ 
<mailto:patrick.gallinari@lip6.fr>sorbonne-universite.fr, deadline for 
applying : 28-04-2021

-- 
